@Node ConfigFiles "ConfigFiles"

  Config Files
  ============

    Progdir:NewUserAnnouncer.CFG

    e.g. HBBS:Doors/System/NewUserAnnouncer/NewUserAnnouncer.CFG

    @{"MailAccessLevel   " link CFG_MailAccessLevel} - Access level for posted mail message
    @{"MustRead          " link CFG_MustRead       } - Can the users skip this message ?
    @{"To                " link CFG_To             } - Who the mail is written to.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_MailAccessLevel "MailAccessLevel"

  MailAccessLevel=<number>

    E.G.

    MailAccessLevel=250

    Default is 50, if default is NOT specified a message will be logged
    in the BBS Error Log file.

    This option determines the minimum access level a user must have in
    order for them to read the message that the NUA door posts.

    Normally you'll set this to a VALID access level that is the one
    above the new user's access level.

    e.g.

    New Users are given access level 10,
    Normal users are given access level 50

    So you would set MailAccessLevel=50 so that NewUsers can't read
    message about other users that have also joined.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_MustRead "MustRead"

  MustRead=<boolean>

    E.G.

    MustRead=NO

    Default is YES

    This specifies if the message can be skipped during a mailscan.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_To "To"

  To=<string>

    E.G.

    To=SYSOP

    Default is "ALL"

    This specified who the message is written to, so if you have a user
    on your bbs who manages accounts then you can specify their handle here

    You can have the message written to multiple users by seperating their
    handles with a comma (,)  e.g. To=SYSOP,ALL,Hydra

@EndNode

